Suspected bandits on Tuesday night stormed the residence of the chairman of the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU), Federal University Gusau (FUG) branch, Malam Abdulrahman Adamu, in the Damba area of Gusau metropolis and kidnapped five members of his family. The Information Officer of the university Umar Usman confirmed the incident in a telephone chat with our correspondent yesterday. According to him, the bandits kidnapped Malam Abbas Umar who is a neighbour of the ASUU chairman during the attack. Umar said the bandits launched the attack on the residents of ASUU chairman on Tuesday.   Gunmen kidnap 11 Abia council workers     Police rescue 113 children from Kano illegal rehabilitation…     N11.79b dispute: Court includes cryptocurrency in Ajetunmobi…   Read Also: Police rescue victims of human trafficking, repel bandits’ attack in Katsina - Advertisement - “The bandits besieged the residence of ASUU chairman on Tuesday night, according to report reaching us and abducted five members of his family and his neighbour Malam Abbas Umar,” Umar Usman confirmed. The FUG image-maker stated that the bandits were on a mission to abduct the ASUU chairman but he escaped by a hair’s breadth. However, efforts made to contact the Zamfara State Police Command Public Relations Officer Sp Muhammad Shehu for confirmation of the incident were not successful.